🎯 PROJECT NAME

Time Audit Engine — Personal 24h Discipline & Planning System

🎯 CORE GOAL

Build a production-grade, single-user, deterministic daily time tracking + planning system that:

Enforces full 24-hour accountability

Detects time gaps

Categorizes time by productivity type

Integrates time-bound daily planning

Compares planned vs actual execution

Generates live, server-confirmed reports

Supports strict mode enforcement

Remains MongoDB free-tier safe

This is NOT a habit tracker.
This is a Planning + Execution Intelligence Engine.

🧱 CORE PRINCIPLES

Day = 00:00 → 24:00 (1440 minutes)

Every minute must be accounted for (execution layer).

Plans and execution are separate layers.

Gaps are detected automatically.

No overlapping blocks allowed.

Reports update only after server confirmation.

Strict Mode prevents closing incomplete days.

Micro-block support (minimum 1 minute).

Planner supports time-bound tasks.

🗂 DATABASE STRUCTURE (MongoDB)
1️⃣ Collection: time_blocks

Reality layer.

{
  _id,
  date: "YYYY-MM-DD",
  startMinutes: Number,
  endMinutes: Number,
  durationMinutes: Number,
  categoryId: ObjectId,
  note: String,
  source: "manual" | "timer",
  createdAt
}


Rules:

start < end

no overlap

duration = end - start (server-calculated only)

2️⃣ Collection: days

Daily summary layer.

{
  _id: "YYYY-MM-DD",

  totalLoggedMinutes,
  totalUntrackedMinutes,
  totalProductiveMinutes,
  totalNeutralMinutes,
  totalWasteMinutes,

  isCompleted: Boolean,

  createdAt,
  updatedAt
}


Auto-created when first block inserted.

Used for:

Strict Mode

Daily report

Completion locking

3️⃣ Collection: categories
{
  _id,
  name,
  type: "productive" | "neutral" | "waste",
  isActive: true,
  createdAt
}

4️⃣ Collection: settings

Single document.

{
  strictMode: true,
  autoPrefillNext: true,
  minBlockMinutes: 1
}

5️⃣ Collection: plans ✅ NEW

Planning layer.

{
  _id,

  date: "YYYY-MM-DD",

  title: String,
  description?: String,

  categoryId?: ObjectId,

  plannedMinutes: Number,   // expected duration

  priority: "low" | "medium" | "high",

  status: "pending" | "done" | "migrated",

  createdAt,
  updatedAt
}


Important:

Plans do NOT auto-create time blocks.

Plans represent intention.
Time blocks represent reality.

🔄 PLAN vs EXECUTION INTELLIGENCE

